","text":"Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole."},{"version":"blue","text":"Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole."},{"version":"yellow","text":"The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest."},{"version":"gold","text":"It can freely de\u00ad tach its jaw to swallow large prey whole. It can be\u00ad come too heavy to move, however."},{"version":"silver","text":"It always hides in grass. When first born, it has no poison, so its bite is painful, but harmless."},{"version":"crystal","text":"It flutters the tip of its tongue to seek out the scent of prey, then swallows the prey whole."},{"version":"ruby","text":"EKANS curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. Assuming this position allows it to quickly respond to a threat from any direction with a glare from its upraised head."},{"version":"sapphire","text":"EKANS curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. Assuming this position allows it to quickly respond to a threat from any direction with a glare from its upraised head."},{"version":"emerald","text":"An EKANS curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. This position allows it to quickly respond to an enemy from any direction with a threat from its upraised head."},{"version":"firered","text":"A very common sight in grassland, etc. It flicks its tongue in and out to sense danger in its surroundings."},{"version":"leafgreen","text":"Moving silently and stealthily, it eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole."},{"version":"diamond","text":"It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind."},{"version":"pearl","text":"It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind."},{"version":"platinum","text":"It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind."},{"version":"heartgold","text":"It can freely detach its jaw to swallow large prey whole. It can become too heavy to move, however."},{"version":"soulsilver","text":"It always hides in grass. When first born, it has no poison, so its bite is painful, but harmless."},{"version":"black","text":"It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind."},{"version":"white","text":"It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind."},{"version":"black-2","text":"It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind."},{"version":"white-2","text":"It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind."},{"version":"x","text":"The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest."},{"version":"y","text":"Moving silently and stealthily, it eats the eggs of birds, such as Pidgey and Spearow, whole."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"Ekans curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. Assuming this position allows it to quickly respond to a threat from any direction with a glare from its upraised head."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"Ekans curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. Assuming this position allows it to quickly respond to a threat from any direction with a glare from its upraised head."},{"version":"ultra-sun","text":"By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests."},{"version":"ultra-moon","text":"The eggs of bird Pok\u00e9mon are its favorite food. It swallows eggs whole, so sometimes an egg gets stuck, and Ekans faints."},{"version":"lets-go-pikachu","text":"The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest."},{"version":"lets-go-eevee","text":"The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest."}],"evo":{"name":"ekans","level":0,"min_level"